<doc id="725106" wikidata="Q5610187" url="?curid=725106" title="Gromov's compactness theorem">
<text>Gromov&#x27;s compactness theorem can refer to either of two mathematical theorems:

* Gromov&#x27;s compactness theorem (geometry) stating that certain sets of Riemannian manifolds are relatively compact in the Gromov-Hausdorff metric
* Gromov&#x27;s compactness theorem (topology) on the existence of limits of sequences of pseudoholomorphic curves</text><links>
<link wikidata="Q5610188" start="87" end="131" title="Gromov&amp;#x27;s compactness theorem (geometry)" label="Gromov&amp;#x27;s compactness theorem (geometry)"/>
